        <p><em>Last Updated: March 2025</em></p>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
            <p><strong>Server & User Data:</strong> We may collect and store necessary data, including Server IDs, Channel IDs, and User IDs, to operate Anya’s features.</p>
            <p><strong>No Personal Information:</strong> Anya does not collect personally identifiable information (PII) such as email addresses, passwords, or financial data.</p>
            <p><strong>Logging & Analytics:</strong> We may collect anonymized usage data to improve Anya’s performance.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
            <p>Data is used to provide music playback, manage preferences, enhance performance, and prevent abuse.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Data Storage & Security</h2>
            <p>We retain data only as long as necessary and implement security measures to protect it.</p>
            <p>Anya may interact with third-party APIs, which have their own privacy policies.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. User Control & Data Removal</h2>
            <p>Users can remove Anya from their server at any time. Data deletion requests can be made via our support team.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h2>5. Policy Updates</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy at any time. Continued use of Anya implies acceptance of changes.</p>
